# LeakSanitizer suppressions for HAZE tests.
#
# Allocations inside libnbcc (niobium-compiler) leak under ASAN — every
# stop_epoch() invocation drops ~2.5 KB inside the optimization passes.
# These leaks are upstream and outside HAZE's control. Suppressing them
# here lets `detect_leaks=1` runs surface any HAZE-side leak immediately.
#
# Usage: LSAN_OPTIONS=suppressions=$(pwd)/.lsan_suppressions ./build-asan/haze_tests
#
# To audit upstream impact, run with the suppression off:
# LSAN_OPTIONS=detect_leaks=1 ./build-asan/haze_tests
#
# When libnbcc fixes these, delete this file and re-run a clean leak pass.

leak:niobium::llvm::optimization::RegisterAllocationPass::transform
leak:niobium::llvm::optimization::OptimizationPass::run
leak:niobium::llvm::Generator::execute
leak:libnbcc.so
